The declaration itself does not violate Rule 8.13 as written because it is an object definition (an array) rather than a pointer type and there is no evidence the table must be immutable. Rule 8.13 applies to pointer types: if an object is only ever read and never modified, it should be declared const so that pointers to it can be const-qualified. A concrete violation scenario would be if OS_impl_filehandle_table is conceptually read-only (never modified at runtime) but is declared as a non-const array: in that case it should be declared as

const OS_impl_file_internal_record_t OS_impl_filehandle_table[OS_MAX_NUM_OPEN_FILES];

so that any pointer obtained to its elements can (and should) point to a const-qualified type. As provided, however, there is no clear MISRA 8.13 violation.
